The paper proposes a novel approach for machine comprehension question answering, which involves high-level reasoning processes of understanding and tracking the relevant contents across various semantic units such as words, phrases, and sentences in a document. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to natural language processing (NLP), artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (ML), and computer vision (CV). 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it covers NLP and information retrieval. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers various aspects of AI, including reasoning, learning, and perception. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as it covers ML algorithms and techniques. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as it covers neural network-based models. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely category but still possible as it covers image and video analysis, which could be relevant to the QA task.
